- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper presents a new numerical method for simulating surgical procedures, which involves developing software to implement the method. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper presents a method for simulating physical processes (needle insertion) in complex geometries (brain and liver models), which is relevant to computational engineering and science. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents a new numerical method for solving partial differential equations, which is relevant to numerical analysis. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions using binary images to obtain surface details of the simulated object, which is relevant to computer vision.
